; Regression test for issue #1145: Using 'bucket' bypass lots of checks/features (BZ#1145)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1145
;
; The bug was that using the 'bucket' directive bypasses certain checks that
; apply to regular postings. One specific manifestation: when using --strict
; mode with declared accounts, the bucket account is implicitly declared by
; the bucket directive itself, so no "Unknown account" warning should be
; produced for the bucket account. The bucket-created posting should still
; balance the transaction correctly.
;
; This test verifies that bucket works correctly with --strict mode:
; the bucket account is treated as implicitly declared.

account Expenses:Food
commodity $

bucket Assets:Checking

2024/01/01 Groceries
    Expenses:Food    $50.00

test bal --strict
             $-50.00  Assets:Checking
              $50.00  Expenses:Food
--------------------
                   0
end test
